- specifies the accessibility(scope) of methods, fields,classes or constructor

Types of modifiers
1. Access modifiers
	Types of Access modifiers:
	a) private
		- only accessible within class,we cannot access from outside the class
		- a class can not be private

	b) default
		- only accessible within the package, we cannot accessed from outside the class
		- if do not specifies access modifiers,it will be default

	c) protected
		- within the package & outside the package through the inheritance only

	d) public
		- access everywhere

2. Non-Access modifiers
	a) static
	b) abstract
	c) synchronised
	d) native
	e) volatile
	f) transient
